core.functions.dev_utils.books.mapmaker_: Likewise, in multiplayer, for playthroughs of 3 or more players, I recommend playing this map without keepInventory on Normal.  This map is designed to be tough on Normal difficulty - Hard is significantly more challenging and not recommended.
For both single and multiplayer - learn to use the special campfires.  These are basically special beds scattered around the world that set your spawnpoint.  Use and abuse them.
This is a short book containing some of my thoughts about how to best enjoy this map based on whether you're in singleplayer or multiplayer.

Playing this map in singleplayer is significantly harder than in multiplayer given the lack of help and less players to fight bosses with.

In this case, there's no shame in playing with Keep-Inventory and using Easy difficulty.  Prioritize having fun first.

I don't recommend hoarding consumable loot.  There's lots of magic scrolls and loot in the world.  If you want to throw 16 lightning scrolls at a single enemy because it's funny, I highly encourage you to do so because there's probably a chest with more scrolls 20 blocks away.

Lastly - this map might appear to have different 'classes' but this is only an illusion - use everything you find.  This map is built for fast-paced gameplay with the opportunity to pull off crazy combos using combinations of all the custom items.

Our humanity has forever been sealed away.  We are stronger now.  We should look towards the future - a future that will soon be mine to control.

But, though my human body has been purged, there is still weakness in me...

My body is strong but my mind is weak.  I feel my pathetic old self pulling on me - my human sentimentality and emotion acting as a weight keeping me from doing what is necessary.  I must be able to sacrifice everything and everyone to achieve my ambition!

I cannot afford to let this weakness linger.  I intend to bury this pathetic remnant of our origins deep underground and have placed a curse on the entrance - only a true beast of both body and soul will be able to open the way.  A beast able to handle any burden.

Only once this beast of burden stands near the lonely palm tree within the canyon and chants the sacred words "We Built Different" will the way forward open.

Forever will we remain beasts with this impossible riddle guarding the path!

item.written_book.17.page.1.1:
1: Beginnings

For a long while, perhaps the longest while of them all, there was nothing.  Then, the Old Gods came to our world and decided there should be something.  So rather than nothing, there were now some things.
item.written_book.17.page.2.1:
...and so it was for a time.  The land, people, and rules of our reality were shaped by the Old Gods.  

We existed under their guidance.  Though rarely did mortals feel their influence.
item.written_book.17.page.3.1:
2: War for Divinity

The Old Gods were not content to sit and relish in their creation.  They sought a new universe, new blank canvases for which to paint.  In leaving this world, they meant to leave to us a token of their divine power.
item.written_book.17.page.4.1:
The crown of God King was made.  The Old Gods were content to observe both man and beast alike contest for the crown amongst themselves.

Kings, warlords, and scum all vied for the ultimate power.  A time of great suffering and pain ensued.
item.written_book.17.page.5.1:
3: An Unlikely Hero

While the conflict continued, a young boy emerged amidst the armies of men and beast to challenge for the crown.  His heart knew not the allure of power and ultimate control.  He only wished for an end to the war.
item.written_book.17.page.6.1:
One by one, the boy overcame all challengers.  Through his strength of will and creativity, towering beasts and powerful kings were bested in combat.

He soon stood alone before the Old Gods.
item.written_book.17.page.7.1:
The boy took the crown of God King.

...and so the war ended.  The world now his and unlimited power from which to shape it, the God King created an era of peace and prosperity.

item.written_book.18.page.1.1:
Hey kids!  You do know about fire, right?  That stuff that you touch and it goes "ouchy ouch!"  Wow!  Hey maybe don't touch that stuff!

That is, unless you have fire resistance on!  Then it's okay, play with it all you want!
item.written_book.18.page.2.1:
Nice!  Now you're playing with fire - literally!  How fun.  Make sure to show your parents this one cool trick.  

But wait, you do know the difference between normal fire and "magic fire", don't you?
item.written_book.18.page.3.1: You little idiot, you need to know the difference!  Fire resistance won't help against the blue fire - aka the Magic Fire.  If you try using that while playing with the blue fire, you'll die a horrible death!  We wouldn't want to show your parents that now would we?
item.written_book.18.page.4.1:
After all, there are plenty of terrible monsters out there that use just such an attack.  Don't play with them!  

So just remember this helpful mnemonic:
F - Fire flame
I - I'm OK!
R - Really blue flame
E - Ehhh I'm not OK!
item.written_book.18.page.5.1:
That's all!  Hey, thanks for reading kids.

Remember, a glass of fire resistance a day keeps the lava away.  But it also introduces numerous side effects that only manifest later in life - such as tuberculosis!

Be safe out there!

It began innocently enough, with a lazy sunday afternoon.  The sound of laughter echoed from our family room.  I was initially glad she was happy.  Her happiness was my happiness.  I would see in her eyes, a curiosity yet 
unseen.
item.written_book.67.page.10.1:
As I stood there in silence, Shrek 2 continued to play in the background.

Almost as if to question Mike Myers on the location of my Emma, I looked into the screen.
item.written_book.67.page.11.1:
It was only more a moment.  

Fiona stood there, Shrek's arms around her.  But instead of Fiona, I could only make out Emma's face.

The love montage scene continued to play.
item.written_book.67.page.12.1:
The television lost power.  

I turned it back on but was met with a rerun of Cars 4.
  
The tow truck made a funny joke about Lightning McQueen having no reproductive organs.
item.written_book.67.page.13.1:
5.

In the months that followed, a missing persons report was filed.  But I knew in my heart she would never be found.
item.written_book.67.page.14.1:
...


My sweetest Emma, I hope you have found your paradise.
item.written_book.67.page.2.1: From that moment Shrek 2 was a constant presence in both mine and Emma's life.  She regaled in Mike Myer's classic voice acting.  Adored Eddie Murphy's relatable humour.  Shrek and Fiona's tale playing out on our screen became a common event in our household.
item.written_book.67.page.3.1:
2.

Emma's passion soon evolved beyond mere appreciation.  It evoled into a nightly ritual that took precedence over our conversations.  Our son ceased to exist.  There was only shrek.

Only shrek.
item.written_book.67.page.4.1: I must admit, seeing her so in love and happy, enchanted and living a life in another world that even after our son started to notice the absence in his life, I resisted stopping it.  I...  Let Mike Myers govern my household for the time being.
item.written_book.67.page.5.1:
3.

I had to stop this.  It was madness.  

I left our son with my parents.  I approached her intending to broach the subject.  As we sat down amidst the swamp-themed decor of our living room, I spoke to her.
item.written_book.67.page.6.1:
"My love, perhaps we could...  Diversify our movie viewings?"

She looked at me.  I tried to look back but could only see Shrek.

"My dear, Shrek is love, Shrek is Life."  She held her gaze, her words cutting like a knife.
item.written_book.67.page.7.1:
"In a world where everything is changing, where I can't tell reality from fiction, Shrek is the only constant.  He is my everything.  He is...  my God."

I had never heard Emma speak with such conviction before.
item.written_book.67.page.8.1:
4.

I awoke the following day after our discussion.  As I descended the stairwell expecting to see her in the family room, I was instead met with an empty household.
item.written_book.67.page.9.1:
My wife was nowhere to be found.

A million thoughts poured through my mind in that moment.  She had not left her seat for months.  Not since Shrek took over our lives.
